          <div class="title">
            <h1 class="title">House sparrow example</h1>
            
            
          </div>

          <div><h1>Case study – birds from the UK</h1><p>In this example, we will build a map of the observations of birds from the United Kingdom.</p></div>

<pre class='hljl'>
<span class='hljl-k'>using</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-n'>GBIF</span>
</pre>



<div><h2>Getting the data</h2><p>The first thing is to specify the <code>taxonKey</code> – this is explained in the [GBIF taxonomy]<a href="but lookup feature will be added to the package later">tax</a>, and the country (<code>GB</code>). Because the GBIF API cannot return more than 200000 records (that&#39;s already quite a lot, but common species have been observed far more), we will (i) focus on a single common species (the House sparrow, <code>5231190</code>), and only observations for the year 2015.</p><p>[tax]: http://www.gbif.org/species/search?dataset_key=d7dddbf4-2cf0-4f39-9b2a-bb099caae36c</p></div>

<pre class='hljl'>
<span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds_query</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-oB'>=</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-nf'>Dict</span><span class='hljl-p'>(</span><span class='hljl-t'>
  </span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;taxonKey&quot;</span><span class='hljl-oB'>=&gt;</span><span class='hljl-ni'>5231190</span><span class='hljl-p'>,</span><span class='hljl-t'>
  </span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;country&quot;</span><span class='hljl-oB'>=&gt;</span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;GB&quot;</span><span class='hljl-p'>,</span><span class='hljl-t'>
  </span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;hasCoordinate&quot;</span><span class='hljl-oB'>=&gt;</span><span class='hljl-kc'>true</span><span class='hljl-p'>,</span><span class='hljl-t'>
  </span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;year&quot;</span><span class='hljl-oB'>=&gt;</span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;2015&quot;</span><span class='hljl-p'>)</span><span class='hljl-t'>
</span><span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-oB'>=</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-nf'>occurrences</span><span class='hljl-p'>(</span><span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds_query</span><span class='hljl-p'>)</span><span class='hljl-t'>
</span><span class='hljl-nf'>println</span><span class='hljl-p'>(</span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;There are &quot;</span><span class='hljl-p'>,</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds</span><span class='hljl-oB'>.</span><span class='hljl-n'>count</span><span class='hljl-p'>,</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot; records available&quot;</span><span class='hljl-p'>)</span>
</pre>


<pre class="hljl">
There are 6296 records available
</pre>


<div><p>This is good! We can complete the request. This would take a while, since we are going through interactions 20 at a time. We can speed up the process a little bit, by requesting 200 records on every page. GBIF will not let you ask for more than 200 records by page.</p></div>

<pre class='hljl'>
<span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds</span><span class='hljl-oB'>.</span><span class='hljl-n'>query</span><span class='hljl-p'>[</span><span class='hljl-s'>&quot;limit&quot;</span><span class='hljl-p'>]</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-oB'>=</span><span class='hljl-t'> </span><span class='hljl-ni'>200</span>
</pre>



<div><p>Let&#39;s now complete the request for real:</p></div>

<pre class='hljl'>
<span class='hljl-nf'>complete!</span><span class='hljl-p'>(</span><span class='hljl-n'>uk_birds</span><span class='hljl-p'>)</span>
</pre>



<div><p>Once this is done, we can start looking at observations. Let&#39;s load the <code>Plots</code> package to help us.</p></div>

<pre class='hljl'>
